⁴⁷ Larem ac penates-J Lar was a Tuscan word, signifying head of his family, or prince of his people. The head of any family or tribe was generally deified after death, and thought to protect the family, and his image was kept in the house. The Lares therefore were of human origin, being no more than the deified ancestors of the family. The Penates were the tutelary gods of the family, and were of divine origin.
